er%20corporate%20job%20to%20pursue%20social%20media%20full-time.%20Callahan%20is%20living%20with%20her%20parents%20to%20save%20up%20money%20and%20move%20to%20Miami.%20The%20conversation%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-class-2020-graduates-future-career-recession-2020-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egraduated%20during%20COVID%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleft-nyc-live-miami-made-me-better-tech-leader-entrepreneur-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eworking%20remotely%20in%20Miami%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20government%20tech%20consultant.%20As%20great%20as%20the%20job%20was%2C%20I%20realized%20it%20wasn't%20fully%20aligned%20with%20what%20I%20wanted%20in%20life.%20I%20was%20sitting%20at%20my%20desk%20all%20day%2C%20watching%20people%20on%20social%20media%20do%20really%20cool%20things%2C%20and%20I%20wanted%20something%20similar%20for%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20wasn't%20working%2C%20I%20was%20posting%20on%20social%20media%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frob-cesternino-survivor-podcast-business-rhap-worth-money-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehosting%20a%20podcast%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20working%20on%20a%20few%20brand%20deals.%20The%20money%20didn't%20compare%20to%20my%20salary%2C%20but%20it%20gave%20me%20hope.%20I%20thought%2C%20%26quot%3BOkay%2C%20worst-case%20scenario%2C%20if%20I%20leave%20my%20job%2C%20I'm%20already%20making%20some%20money%20outside%20my%20salary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20as%20a%20consultant%20for%204%20years%20and%20was%20promoted%20very%20quickly.%20But%20there%20were%20a%20few%20things%20I%20didn't%20like%20about%20my%20job%2C%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdeloitte-cuts-down-benefits-for-some-workers-big-four-ai-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ehaving%20barely%20any%20PTO%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20final%20straw%20came%20when%20I%20was%20offered%20a%20higher-level%20position%20without%20a%20raise%20or%20an%20official%20promotion.%20At%20that%20point%2C%20I%20started%20to%20wonder%20whether%20the%20company%20actually%20cared%20about%20my%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20very%20risk-averse%2C%20but%20I%20put%20in%20my%20notice%20and%20decided%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbecome-content-creator-instagram-tiktok-six-figures-full-time-2022-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epursue%20social%20media%20full-time%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20was%20probably%20the%20riskiest%20move%20I've%20ever%20made.%20My%20family%20thought%20I%20was%20crazy.%20Half%20of%20my%20family%20is%20from%20Mexico%2C%20including%20my%20grandparents%2C%20and%20they%20were%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20are%20you%20doing%3F%20You%20have%20this%20great%20life%20in%20the%20US.%20You%20can't%20give%20it%20up%20for%20this%20crazy%20idea.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20I%20had%20to%20listen%20to%20myself%20and%20trust%20my%20intuition.%20Even%20though%20I%20didn't%20have%20a%20backup%20job%2C%20I%20knew%20that%20to%20get%20more%2C%20I%20had%20to%20do%20more%20and%20take%20bigger%20steps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224ed7a330-77d8-46d4-bab2-f6c23953e7de%5C%22%3EMoving%20in%20with%20my%20parents%20made%20financial%20sense%20while%20I%20switched%20careers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomerang-kids-moving-back-in-with-parents-saving-money-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emoved%20back%20in%20with%20my%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20live%20in%20Northern%20Virginia%2C%20twice%20in%20my%20life.%20The%20first%20time%20was%20in%202023%2C%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnative-floridian-leaves-miami-traffic-rent-high-prices-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EI%20left%20Miami%3C%2Fa%3E%20following%20the%20end%20of%20a%20relationship.%20I%20lived%20with%20them%20until%20August%202024%2C%20when%20I%20eventually%20quit%20my%20tech%20consultant%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Mexican%20culture%2C%20it's%20very%20normal%20for%20kids%20to%20stay%20home%20until%20they're%20married%2C%20so%20my%20parents%20welcomed%20me%20back%20with%20open%20arms.%20Moving%20back%20home%20also%20made%20a%20lot%20of%20sense%20financially%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20family%20of%20four%20pose%20for%20a%20picture%20at%20a%20resturant.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fcc9d6e1443b8dc48e2e30%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECallahan%2C%20on%20the%20far%20right%2C%20with%20her%20family.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Keara%20Callahan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EI%20studied%20economics%20in%20college%2C%20so%20I%20knew%20it%20was%20the%20best%20thing%20for%20my%20budget.%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20to%20pay%20rent%2C%20I%20could%20save%20money%2C%20and%20I%20could%20build%20up%20my%20nest%20egg%20%E2%80%94%20though%20I%20still%20contributed%20around%20the%20house%20by%20helping%20with%20groceries%2C%20chores%2C%20and%20whatever%20else%20was%20needed.%20I%20also%20wanted%20to%20be%20home%20because%20we%20have%20two%20older%20dogs.%20They%20were%20my%20childhood%20pets%2C%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20with%20them%20during%20their%20last%20few%20weeks%20or%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20part%20I%20was%20most%20nervous%20about%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-become-an-influencer-instagram-tiktok-youtube-snapchat%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esharing%20my%20move%20on%20social%20media%3C%2Fa%3E.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20I%20was%2025%2C%20and%20I%20thought%20moving%20back%20home%20would%20be%20embarrassing.%20I%20had%20built%20and%20shared%20this%20picture-perfect%20life%20online%20%E2%80%94%20moving%20to%20big-city%20Miami%2C%20living%20in%20a%20nice%20apartment%20%E2%80%94%20when%2C%20in%20reality%2C%20things%20hadn't%20worked%20out%20that%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHaving%20to%20explain%2C%20%26quot%3BOops%2C%20I'm%20back%20home%2C%26quot%3B%20felt%20scary.%20But%20funny%20enough%2C%20it%20didn't%20turn%20out%20to%20be%20as%20scary%20as%20I%20thought.%20A%20lot%20of%20people%20actually%20felt%20the%20same%20way.%20Some%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BI'm%20thinking%20about%20doing%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BI%20just%20moved%20back%20in%20too.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20way%2C%20it%20created%20a%20safe%20space%20for%20people%20to%20talk%20about%20moving%20back%20home%20and%20ask%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223648%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20young%20woman%20smiles%20while%20holding%20a%20railing%2C%20overlooking%20a%20large%20body%20of%20water.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fcc9783cfefc31768d6b29%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222432%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECallahan.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Keara%20Callahan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20I%20quit%20my%20job%2C%20I%20was%20already%20living%20at%20home%20with%20my%20parents.%20I%20decided%20to%20start%20traveling%20and%20spent%20eight%20months%20in%20Bali%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftravel-southeast-asia-worst-best-cities-thailand-laos-vietnam-malaysia-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Etraveled%20throughout%20Southeast%20Asia%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Middle%20East%2C%20Europe%2C%20and%20Latin%20America%2C%20visiting%20places%20like%20Malaysia%2C%20Singapore%2C%20Dubai%2C%20Qatar%2C%20France%2C%20Spain%2C%20Mexico%2C%20Argentina%2C%20and%20Uruguay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20documented%20my%20travels%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fkearaacallahan%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eon%20Instagram%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tiktok.com%2F%40kearacallahan%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%20TikTok%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20basis%20of%20my%20social%20media%20content%20comes%20from%20sharing%20my%20own%20experiences.%20And%20since%20I%20had%20never%20traveled%20alone%20before%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20show%20my%20audience%20what%20it%20was%20like%20to%20step%20out%20of%20my%20comfort%20zone%20and%20try%20new%2C%20unfamiliar%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%224abcc070-37d7-4272-a4f8-6555c7ef4f1b%5C%22%3ELiving%20at%20home%20helped%20me%20save%20money%20to%20move%20out%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20traveling%2C%20I%20moved%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fboomerang-kids-moving-back-in-with-parents-saving-money-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eback%20in%20with%20my%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20past%20March.%20Within%20a%20few%20months%2C%20I'll%20be%20moving%20back%20to%20Miami%20and%20getting%20my%20own%20apartment.%20I%20wouldn't%20have%20been%20able%20to%20save%20up%20as%20quickly%20without%20having%20my%20parents'%20home%20as%20a%20place%20to%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224284%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20mom%20and%20a%20daughter%20smile%20for%20a%20picture%20while%20sitting%20at%20a%20restaurant%2C%20the%20daughter%20has%20a%20coffee%20in%20her%20hand.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fcc9273cfefc31768d6b25%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223213%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECallahan%2C%20right%2C%20with%20her%20mother.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Keara%20Callahan%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20much%20has%20surprised%20me%20the%20second%20time%20around%2C%20except%20my%20parents'%20willingness%20to%20adapt%20to%20my%20lifestyle.%20We%20go%20on%20walks%20together%20now%2C%20and%20it%20feels%20like%20they%20genuinely%20want%20to%20do%20things%20like%20that%20with%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hardest%20part%20has%20been%20adjusting%20to%20being%20back%20in%20someone%20else's%20home.%20You%20get%20used%20to%20living%20life%20your%20own%20way%20%E2%80%94%20eating%20what%20you%20want%2C%20keeping%20your%20own%20routine%2C%20and%20doing%20things%20on%20your%20own%20schedule.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20downside%20is%20that%20I%20don't%20have%20many%20friends%20in%20the%20town%20where%20they%20live.%20Most%20people%20have%20moved%20away%20or%20gotten%20jobs%20elsewhere%2C%20so%20if%20I'm%20not%20spending%20time%20with%20my%20parents%2C%20I%20don't%20really%20have%20anyone%20else%20to%20hang%20out%20with.%20It%20has%20made%20our%20relationship%20much%20stronger%2C%20though.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ff036205-a7fa-4d7c-9360-f018d741e5e9%5C%22%3EMoving%20back%20in%20with%20my%20parents%20was%20humbling%2C%20but%20also%20empowering%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20used%20to%20feel%20a%20lot%20of%20pressure%20to%20show%20people%20that%20things%20were%20going%20well%20in%20my%20life.%20But%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmultigenerational-living-build-wealth-elder-care-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emoving%20back%20in%20with%20my%20parents%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20traveling%20helped%20me%20realize%20that%20the%20timeline%20we%20put%20on%20ourselves%20doesn't%20really%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20met%2040-year-olds%20going%20back%20to%20school%20and%2020-year-olds%20doing%20their%20own%20thing.%20I%20realized%20I%20don't%20have%20to%20have%20everything%20figured%20out%2C%20and%20I%20know%20there's%20always%20somewhere%20I%20can%20go%20if%20things%20fall%20apart%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-my-corporate-job-over-text-after-burning-out-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EQuitting%20my%20corporate%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20moving%20back%20in%20also%20increased%20my%20confidence%20tenfold.%20When%20I%20first%20quit%2C%20I%20was%20scared%20about%20where%20money%20would%20come%20from.%20I%20had%20to%20figure%20it%20out%20quickly%2C%20and%20that%20made%20me%20more%20willing%20to%20take%20risks%2C%20try%20new%20things%2C%20and%20put%20myself%20out%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIdeally%2C%20I%20want%20to%20stay%20%3