thor's%20grandma%20fought%20to%20have%20guardianship%20over%20her.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20after%20years%20of%20court%20proceedings%2C%20her%20petition%20was%20denied.%20In%20her%2070s%20with%20her%20own%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsymptoms-you-should-never-ignore-2019-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emedical%20issues%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20deal%20with%2C%20she%20was%20deemed%20%26quot%3Bunfit%26quot%3B%20to%20take%20care%20of%20a%2014-year-old%20who%20walked%20with%20a%20cane%20for%20balance%20support.%20Yet%20she%20refused%20to%20let%20that%20stop%20her%20from%20being%20the%20most%20important%20person%20in%20my%20life.%20Since%20she%20lived%20less%20than%20two%20miles%20away%20from%20my%20high%20school%2C%20we'd%20meet%20at%20least%20three%20times%20a%20week%20to%20spend%20a%20few%20hours%20together%20before%20I%20headed%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221f67f8f0-8a86-4b0f-86eb-b270618df76a%5C%22%3EI%20felt%20like%20a%20burden%20to%20her%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EShe'd%20ask%20about%20my%20classes%2C%20then%20tell%20me%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchildren-who-practice-this-hobby-are-more-likely-to-be-successful-as-adults-2016-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emusic%20classes%3C%2Fa%3E%20she%20was%20taking%20to%20finish%20her%20degree%20belatedly.%20Her%20love%20of%20learning%20and%20encouragement%20inspired%20me%20to%20achieve%20my%20goals.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20high%20school%2C%20I%20worked%20hard%20to%20make%20the%20Dean's%20List.%20She%20rewarded%20me%20with%20a%20new%20dress%20and%20an%20allowance%2C%20which%20I%20used%20to%20buy%20school%20lunches%20and%20books.%20She%20made%20each%20of%20my%20birthdays%20special%2C%20too%2C%20bringing%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fina-garten-favorite-chocolate-cake-recipe%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efavorite%20chocolate%20cake%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20singing%20the%20song%20she'd%20taught%20me%2C%20Tony%20Bennett's%20%26quot%3BI%20Left%20My%20Heart%20in%20San%20Francisco.%26quot%3B%20This%20was%20more%20than%20a%20sweet%20treat%3B%20she%20gave%20me%20the%20only%20sense%20of%20stability%20I%20had%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20I%20silently%20carried%20the%20weight%20of%20feeling%20like%20a%20burden%20to%20my%20grandma%20until%20my%20college%20orientation.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20like%20the%20daughter%20I%20never%20had%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20whispered%2C%20thanking%20me%20for%20giving%20her%20a%20second%20chance%20to%20be%20a%20more%20involved%20parent%2C%20since%20her%20job%20took%20up%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20while%20her%20boys%20were%20growing%20up%2C%20she%20said.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20moment%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20was%20living%20the%20relationship%20I%20had%20yearned%20for%20since%20I%20was%20a%20child%20%E2%80%94%20a%20healthy%20mother-daughter%20bond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229f9dae68-210e-4b7b-b29c-de2f4ba6d334%5C%22%3EI%20cared%20for%20her%20when%20she%20got%20older%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20time%20that%20I%20finished%20my%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funemployed-recent-college-grad-applied-thousand-jobs-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emaster's%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Marion's%20diagnosis%20of%20arthritis%20progressed%20severely%2C%20impacting%20her%20ability%20to%20walk.%20When%20my%20grandfather%2C%20Joe%2C%20who%20physically%20took%20care%20of%20her%2C%20was%20hospitalized%2C%20everything%20changed.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20their%20quality%20of%20life%20diminished%2C%20my%20level%20of%20responsibility%20increased.%20It%20wasn't%20until%20she%20had%20a%20heart%20attack%20in%202022%20that%20I%20realized%20I%20should%20step%20up%20to%20take%20care%20of%20her.%20By%20age%2033%2C%20I%20started%20handling%20her%20insurance%20claims%20and%20became%20the%20point%20of%20contact%20as%20her%20healthcare%20proxy%20and%20power%20of%20attorney.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKnowing%20that%20no%20one%20else%20cared%20about%20her%20as%20much%20as%20I%20did%20gave%20me%20comfort.%20I%20researched%20the%20best%20doctors%20available%20through%20her%20insurance%20and%20became%20her%20advocate%20during%20appointments.%20I%20ensured%20that%20she%20and%20my%20grandfather%20received%20the%20best%20care.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%2090s%2C%20the%20woman%20who%20ate%20organic%20food%20before%20it%20was%20trendy%20and%20rarely%20saw%20doctors%20needed%20frequent%20appointments%20and%20physical%20assistance%20for%20her%20basic%20needs.%20With%20time%20and%20research%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20secure%20her%20a%20place%20in%20a%20five-star%20rehabilitation%20home.%20I%20secured%20the%20only%20double%20room%20in%20the%20facility%20so%20she%20and%20my%20grandfather%20could%20stay%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENaively%2C%20I%20hoped%20that%20rehab%20would%20fix%20her%2C%20but%20it%20turned%20out%20that%20assisted%20living%20was%20necessary%20when%20she%20turned%2094.%20From%20then%20on%2C%20I%20learned%20how%20to%20balance%20my%20life%20with%20the%20bureaucracy%20of%20aging%20facilities%2C%20making%20sure%20I%20kept%20up%20with%20the%20rapid%20changes%20for%20my%20grandma's%20needs.%20Each%20Mother's%20Day%2C%20I%20bought%20her%20a%20dress.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20year%20later%2C%20she%20was%20placed%20in%20hospice%2C%20and%20I%20visited%20her%20all%20the%20time.%20On%20her%2096%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%20birthday%2C%20I%20brought%20her%20a%20chocolate%20cake%2C%20and%20we%20sang%20her%20favorite%20song.%20%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EUnlike%20my%20parents%2C%20who'd%20died%20suddenly%20away%20from%20me%2C%20when%20Grandma%20Marion%20died%20two%20months%20later%2C%20it%20was%20in%20my%20arms.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20seemed%20fitting%2C%20since%20she%20was%20the%20one%20who%20taught%20me%20what%20love%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrandmothe