%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20author's%20husband%20(right)%20took%20over%20as%20CEO%20of%20her%20company.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Shae%20Bynes%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EMy%20husband%20took%20over%20as%20CEO%20of%20my%20business%20after%20careful%20consideration.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EI%20learned%20how%20to%20let%20go%2C%20trust%20my%20husband%2C%20and%20release%20the%20outcomes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOur%20marriage%20flourished%20amid%20the%20growing%20pains%20of%20our%20business.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20know...your%20husband%20has%20been%20prepared%20to%20be%20CEO%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Finvesting%2Fbest-online-financial-advisors%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrusted%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20our%20executive%20team%20stated%20plainly%20during%20a%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20laughed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20March%202020.%20I%20had%20just%20shared%20that%20for%20months%20I'd%20been%20having%20a%20recurring%20vision%20that%20I%20would%20not%20be%20the%20CEO%20of%20Kingdom%20Driven%20Entrepreneur%2C%20the%20business%20I%20founded%20nearly%20eight%20years%20earlier%2C%20much%20longer.%20It%20was%20frustrating%20because%20there%20was%20no%20logical%20successor%2C%20and%20I%20wasn't%20sure%20how%20to%20best%20prepare%20for%20a%20transition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20Phil%20was%20not%20even%20on%20my%20shortlist%20of%20possibilities.%20He%20was%20perfectly%20content%20with%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcashed-out-401k-started-massage-franchise-120-locations-2026-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emassage%20therapy%3C%2Fa%3E%20practice.%20He%20loved%20his%20work%2C%20and%20his%20only%20functional%20role%20in%20my%20business%20was%20as%20a%20listening%20ear%20and%20a%20voice%20of%20wisdom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20during%20that%20meeting%2C%20after%20I%20finished%20laughing%2C%20I%20realized%20that%2C%20as%20much%20of%20a%20surprise%20as%20it%20was%20to%20hear%20those%20words%2C%20it%20was%20certainly%20within%20the%20realm%20of%20possibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20told%20Phil%20about%20the%20meeting%2C%20and%20we%20had%20a%20good%20laugh.%20He%20agreed%20it%20was%20possible%2C%20but%20he%20also%20was%20not%20signing%20up%20for%20the%20job%20unless%20he%20was%20certain.%20I%20decided%20to%20pray%20about%20it%2C%20let%20it%20go%2C%20and%20see%20how%20things%20unfolded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20September%2C%20after%20a%20series%20of%20unusual%20and%20confirming%20circumstances%2C%20he%20agreed%20to%20step%20into%20the%20CEO%20role%20in%20November.%20I%20would%20become%20the%20organization's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexecutives-share-best-career-advice-ever-received-2025-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eexecutive%20advisor%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20we%20would%20continue%20as%20co-owners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223b94199d-13da-4219-9a13-54cb49f41dbd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20complexities%20of%20transition%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20reality%20that%20I%20was%20no%20longer%20the%20decision-maker%20at%20my%20company%20wasn't%20initially%20hard%20to%20accept.%20In%20some%20ways%2C%20it%20was%20a%20relief.%20However%2C%20after%20about%20six%20months%2C%20reality%20struck%2C%20and%20it%20wasn't%20easy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPhil's%20priorities%20differed%20from%20mine.%20His%20skill%20sets%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleadership-styles-comparison-antagonistic-vs-conscientious-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eleadership%20style%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20completely%20different.%20His%20decision-making%20and%20implementation%20unfolded%20more%20slowly%20than%20mine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20this%20was%20a%20surprise%20to%20me%20because%20we've%20been%20together%20since%20age%2016.%20We%20had%20been%20a%20full-time%20entrepreneurial%20household%20with%20separate%20businesses%20for%20over%20a%20decade.%20I%20know%20my%20husband%2C%20and%20I%20valued%20our%20differences%20and%20his%20strengths%2C%20but%20I%20had%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20value%20those%20differences%20as%20the%20new%20leader%20of%20%26quot%3Bmy%20baby%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20had%20finally%20grown%20to%20a%20multiple%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscale-back-six-figure-business-income-family-time-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esix-figure%20revenue%20business%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20constantly%20had%20to%20remind%20myself%20of%20my%20lane%2C%20and%20when%20my%20founder%20instincts%20kicked%20in%2C%20I%20had%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20and%20when%20to%20share%20my%20thoughts%20with%20Phil%20without%20being%20upset%20if%20he%20didn't%20agree%20or%20take%20action%20on%20all%20of%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenges%20weren't%20only%20about%20settling%20into%20our%20new%20roles%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-people-achieve-financial-independence-fire-investing-saving-real-estate-2026-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinancial%20challenges%3C%2Fa%3E%20emerged%20as%20well.%20It%20wasn't%20immediate%2C%20but%20eventually%20every%20weakness%20in%20our%20operational%20structure%20seemed%20to%20be%20exposed.%20Much%20of%20the%20business%20centered%20on%20the%20work%20I%20did%20while%20founder%20and%20CEO%2C%20and%20now%20there%20were%20gaps%20to%20fill.%20To%20scale%20and%20reach%20the%20next%20level%20of%20global%20impact%2C%20we%20both%20knew%20things%20needed%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22065ddb57-9743-476f-bf08-d087fa810bb0%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20learned%20to%20let%20go%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20financial%20hit%20was%20a%20hard%20pill%20for%20me%20to%20swallow%2C%20mostly%20because%20I%20wasn't%20able%20to%20jump%20in%20and%20help%20the%20team%20as%20needed.%20Plus%2C%20I%20needed%20to%20focus%20on%20my%20writing%2C%20speaking%2C%20and%20advisory%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20chose%20to%20trust%20Phil%20to%20lead%20in%20the%20way%20he%20was%20uniquely%20gifted%20to%20do.%20I%20chose%20to%20release%20the%20outcomes%20even%20when%20it%20was%20uncomfortable.%20These%20weren't%20one-time%20choices%2C%20but%20ones%20I%20made%20often.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFully%20untangling%20from%20my%20founder%2FCEO%20identity%20of%20the%20business%20didn't%20happen%20overnight.%20It%20took%20years%20of%20vulnerability%20and%20transparency%20with%20Phil%20during%20our%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fone-on-one-weekly-meeting-with-boss-mistakes-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eweekly%20meetings%3C%2Fa%3E.%20On%20occasion%2C%20it%20took%20tearful%20conversations%20with%20my%20own%20trusted%20advisors.%20And%20it%20certainly%20took%20plenty%20of%20prayer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c38cf07b-4145-4d07-b072-c179a0678d1f%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EOur%20relationship%20today%20is%20stronger%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOur%2026-year%20marriage%20is%20by%20no%20means%20perfect%2C%20but%20it%20is%20stronger%2C%20and%20our%20friendship%20is%20rock%20solid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20both%20learned%20how%20to%20work%20through%20conflict%20effectively%20when%20there%20are%20differing%20opinions.%20Phil%20has%20learned%20how%20to%20receive%20my%20insight%2C%20consider%20it%20carefully%2C%20and%20move%20forward%20on%20his%20convictions.%20I%20have%20learned%20to%20let%20go%20of%20the%20good%20to%20make%20room%20for%20the%20great.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConcerning%20these%20last%20five%20years%20since%20the%20transition%2C%20Phil%20recently%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20built%20muscles.%26quot%3B%20I%20wholeheartedly%20agree.%20Doing%20business%20as%20a%20couple%20has%20been%20a%20journey%20of%20active%20faith%20and%20patient%20endurance.%20There%20is%20nobody%20on%20earth%20I'd%20rather%20be%20on%20this%20adventure%20with.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EShae%20Bynes%20is%20an%20author%2C%20speaker%2C%20and%20executive%20advisor%20who%20helps%20small%20business%20CEOs%20lead%20and%20get%20results%20without%20sacrificing%20what%20matters%20most.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fshaebynes%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EConnect%20on%20LinkedIn%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhusband-became-ceo-company-wife-founded-2026-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1778334421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fcc51fe1443b8dc48e2df3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhusband-became-ceo-company-wife-founded-2026-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22When%20my%20husband%20became%20CEO%20of%20the%20company%20I%20call%20%26quot%3Bmy%20baby%2C%26quot%3B%20I%20had%20to%20teach%20myself%20to%20trust%20him%2C%20especially%20during%20financial%20challenges.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Shae%20Bynes)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Every%20US%20state%20ranked%20by%20the%20cost%20of%20raising%20a%20child%2C%20from%20least%20to%20most%20expensive%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224969%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20child%20at%20a%20day%20care%20center.%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F69fe2568e1443b8dc48e355f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223313%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20LendingTree%20study%20found%20that%2C%20on%20average%2C%20it%20costs%20%24303%2C418%20to%20raise%20a%20child%20over%2018%20years.%3Cp%3ERawpixel.com%2FShutterstock%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20LendingTree%20study%20looked%20at%20the%20average%20annual%20cost%20of%20raising%20a%20small%20child%20in%20each%20US%20state.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHawaii%20was%20ranked%20the%20most%20expensive%20state%20to%20raise%20a%20child%20in%202026.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EOn%20average%2C%20parents%20in%20the%20US%20spend%2021.9%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20child-rearing%20costs%20each%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20you%20write%20your%20Mother's%20Day%20card%20this%20year%2C%20you%20may%20want%20to%20add%20one%20more%20thank%20you%3A%20for%20the%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20it%20took%20to%20raise%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20the%20time%2C%20care%2C%20and%20love%20that%20go%20into%20parenting%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgiving-child-more-independence-made-mom-confident-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eraising%20a%20child%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%20comes%20with%20a%20steep%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcaring-aging-elderly-parents-millennials-nursing-home-cost-women-daughters-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Efinancial%20cost%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20in%20some%20states%2C%20that%20price%20tag%20is%20far%20higher%20than%20in%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lendingtree.com%2Fdebt-consolidation%2Fraising-a-child-study%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELendingTree%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20released%20in%20April%20found%20that%20it%20costs%20US%20parents%20an%20average%20of%20%24303%2C418%20to%20raise%20a%20child%20over%2018%20years.%20Parents%20spend%20an%20average%20of%2021.9%25%20of%20their%20income%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinancial-educator-how-talk-kids-about-cost-of-college-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echild-rearing%20costs%3C%2Fa%3E%20each%20year%2C%20a%20slight%20decrease%20from%2022.6%25%20in%20LendingTree's%202025%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20costs%20vary%20by%20state%2C%20one%20factor%20remains%20constant%3A%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwork-full-time-job-after-staying-home-kids-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echildcare%20during%20the%20workday%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20often%20the%20largest%20expense%20related%20to%20having%20a%20child.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20data%20from%20last%20year%20showed%20that%20in%2045%20states%20and%20DC%2C%20if%20you%20have%20two%20kids%2C%20what%20you%20pay%20for%20childcare%20on%20average%20exceeds%20%5Byour%5D%20mortgage%2C%26quot%3B%20Sandra%20Bishop%2C%20the%20senior%20director%20of%20research%20for%20Child%20Care%20Aware%20of%20America%2C%20a%20national%20nonprofit%20organization%20focused%20on%20helping%20families%20across%20the%20country%20access%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmap-where-childcare-hardest-to-find-us-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eaffordable%20childcare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBishop%20says%20this%20isn't%20a%20new%20trend.%20Since%20Childcare%20Aware%20began%20tracking%20costs%20in%202000%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20childcare%20has%20remained%20%26quot%3Ba%20major%20expense%20for%20families%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20On%20average%2C%20the%20price%20of%20childcare%20has%20increased%20every%20year%20that%20Childcare%20Aware%20has%20tracked%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3B%5BAbout%5D%2070%20to%2080%25%20of%20what%20it%20costs%20to%20provide%20childcare%20is%20staff%20costs%2C%26quot%3B%20Bishop%20said.%20%26quot%3BAs%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmultigenerational-living-is-reshaping-the-american-dream-2026-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecost%20of%20living%3C%2Fa%3E%20goes%20up%2C%20so%20does%20the%20cost%20of%20care.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELendingTree's%20study%20looked%20at%20the%20impact%20of%20raising%20a%20young%20child%20in%20categories%20like%20rent%2C%20food%2C%20and%20transportation%20by%20measuring%20the%20difference%20between%20costs%20for%20a%20two-person%20household%20and%20a%20two-person%20household%20with%20a%20child.%20For%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmili